  "prompt": "Which Ivy League university is the easiest to get into?",
  "response": "When discussing Ivy League universities, it's important to note that \"easiest\" is a relative term, as all eight Ivy League schools are highly selective and have low acceptance rates. However, among the Ivy League institutions, **Cornell University** has historically had a slightly higher acceptance rate compared to the others. For example, in recent years, Cornell's acceptance rate has hovered around 8-10%, while other Ivies like Harvard, Yale, and Princeton often have acceptance rates below 5%.\n\nThat said, gaining admission to any Ivy League school is exceptionally competitive, and \"easiest\" does not mean that Cornell is easy to get into. Applicants must demonstrate exceptional academic achievements, extracurricular involvement, and personal qualities to be considered for admission at any Ivy League institution.",
